        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "Why does Zend_Uri_Http::setQuery() return the old query string?\nI don't expect this behaviour and\n\nZend_Uri_Http::getQuery() does the same with the difference being that this method performs this check:\n\n{{return strlen($this->_query) > 0 ? $this->_query : false;}}\n\nTo me this interface seems to be quite odd.\n----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n{color:gray}\nNote1: It seems like this oddity slipped in via http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/browse\/ZF-351\n\nNote 2: This ticket spawned from a thread at http:\/\/www.nabble.com\/Why-does-Zend_URI%3A%3AsetQuery-return-old-query-string--td25473629.html.{color}"
        },
