        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/34490",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=till",
                        "name": "till",
                        "displayName": "Till Klampaeckel",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "This could be a refactoring ticket for 2.0.\n\nAlong with this request, I'd rather see a fluent interface -- like many components provide:\n\n{code}\n$uri->setConfig($foo)->setQuery('foo')->setScheme('http');\n{code}\n\nThen, I'd also like {{isValid()}} instead of {{valid}}. Follows the validator pattern and the accepted convention that the method name is prefixed with {{is}} when they return booleans.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=till",
                        "name": "till",
                        "displayName": "Till Klampaeckel",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-09-16T09:41:48.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-09-16T09:41:48.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/34752",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=shahar",
                        "name": "shahar",
                        "displayName": "Shahar Evron",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I agree, but the API will not change until 2.0\n\nBTW I think Zend_Uri should get a major face lift for 2.0, including some big functionality and purpose changes, separation of all validation work to a Zend_Validate component, support for different URL schemes (even partial URIs and arbitrary schemas), resolving of relative URLs etc. \n\nI made a proposal for that and even wrote some code but without API breakage this is almost impossible, so I dropped it. \n\nShahar.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=shahar",
                        "name": "shahar",
                        "displayName": "Shahar Evron",
                        "active": true
                    },
